records.nl_statement: Define $f_{n}:[0,1] \rightarrow \mathbb{R}$ by the equation $f_{n}(x)=x^{n}$. Show that the sequence $\left(f_{n}(x)\right)$ converges for each $x \in[0,1]$.

records.nl_statement: Suppose $p \in \mathcal{P}(\mathbf{C})$ has degree $m$. Prove that $p$ has $m$ distinct roots if and only if $p$ and its derivative $p^{\prime}$ have no roots in common.

open Fintype Complex Polynomial LinearMap FiniteDimensional Module Module.End
open scoped BigOperators

theorem exercise_4_4 (p : Polynomial ℂ) :
  p.degree = @card (rootSet p ℂ) (rootSetFintype p ℂ) ↔
  Disjoint
  (@card (rootSet (derivative p) ℂ) (rootSetFintype (derivative p) ℂ))
  (@card (rootSet p ℂ) (rootSetFintype p ℂ)) :=
